name: Term 3 Simulator v1.2
body: Adding a timer component that resets after an incident. This way you can track both how careful and how fast your car is.

name: Term 3 Simulator v1.1
body: Mostly just polished and refined some of the Frenet transformation math and made the Car AI more careful.

name: ROS Integration Simulator
body: The final system integration project using ROS integration with the Unity Simulator, with all native platform binaries, using a VM for Windows/MAC to connect to ROS. The project features controls and traffic light detection.

name: Term 3 Simulator v1.0
body: Added an auto grader that tracks how many miles driven without incident. The student should be able to drive at least 4.32 miles without incident to pass.

name: Term 3 Simulator Beta update
body: Fixed the jerk calculation so that it averages over 1 second. Also fixed an instance where s,d value could be NaN and break the JSON object parsing.

name: Term 2 Simulator v1.45
body: Fixed the reset message switch in PID, also optimized the build file where it was referencing some old unused scenes.

name: Term 3 Simulator BETA
body:
Beta version of the Term 3 Simulator featuring the Path Planning Project. The Path Planning starter code and instructions can be found in its repository here, https://github.com/udacity/CarND-Path-Planning-Project.
Note that the simulator source code for this project is not currently available, only the binary files to run the simulator.

name: Term 2 Simulator v1.4
body: Increased the speed limit of the car from 100 MPH to 200 MPH in the control projects. Made some minor menu changes to make Run Away Car a bonus challenge, not a stand alone project. Fixed a timing issue with Project 3: Kidnapped Car and added a timing constraint for passing.

name: Term 2 Simulator V1.3 Updated MPC
body: Updated MPC project. Added the ability to display both MPC predicted  trajectory and waypoints/reference path in the simulator.

name: Term 2 Simulator v1.2 with MPC
body: Adding the MPC project to the Term 2 Simulator

name: Term 2 Simulator First Release
body: Includes all the released Term 2 Projects, Kalman Trackers with EKF and UKF, localization with particle filters, and controls with PID.
